# CI/CD Pipeline template 
![Pipeline](data:image/png;base64,)
Building for Node.js Api using Jenkins & Docker

## Install Java (ubuntu 18.04)


Jenkins required Java jdk so first is installing java.

- Download from https://www.oracle.com/java/technologies/downloads/#java8
- Copy file to Linux server ( If windows use [WinSCP] )
```sh
> sudo mkdir /usr/lib/jvm && cd /usr/lib/jvm
> sudo tar -xvzf ~/jdk-8u311-linux-x64.tar.gz
> sudo vi /etc/environment
```
- Append 3 line below to the end of PATH variable separate with ":" .
```sh
/usr/lib/jvm/jdk1.8.0_311/bin
/usr/lib/jvm/jdk1.8.0_311/db/bin
/usr/lib/jvm/jdk1.8.0_311/jre/bin
```
-  Copy 4 line below as a new line under PATH variable.
```sh
J2SDKDIR="/usr/lib/jvm/jdk1.8.0_311"
J2REDIR="/usr/lib/jvm/jdk1.8.0_311/jre"
JAVA_HOME="/usr/lib/jvm/jdk1.8.0_311"
DERBY_HOME="/usr/lib/jvm/jdk1.8.0_311/db"
```
```sh
> sudo update-alternatives --install "/usr/bin/java" "java" "/usr/lib/jvm/jdk1.8.0_311/bin/java" 0
> sudo update-alternatives --install "/usr/bin/javac" "javac" "/usr/lib/jvm/jdk1.8.0_311/bin/javac" 0
> sudo update-alternatives --set java /usr/lib/jvm/jdk1.8.0_311/bin/java
> sudo update-alternatives --set javac /usr/lib/jvm/jdk1.8.0_311/bin/javac
```
NOTE : <jdk1.8.0_311> name depend on java version.

## Install Jenkins (ubuntu 18.04)
Run command bellow to install Jenkins.
```sh
> wget -q -O - https://pkg.jenkins.io/debian-stable/jenkins.io.key | sudo apt-key add -
> sudo sh -c 'echo deb http://pkg.jenkins.io/debian-stable binary/ > /etc/apt/sources.list.d/jenkins.list'
> sudo apt update
> sudo apt install jenkins
```
## Enable Firewall
enable 8080 (Jenkins running port) to make Jenkins able to access from external ip.

```sh
> sudo ufw allow 8080
```
If never enable UFW try to run
```sh
> sudo ufw allow OpenSSH && sudo ufw enable
```
## Install Docker & Docker compose (ubuntu 18.04)
Run command bellow to install Docker & Docker compose
```sh
> sudo apt update && sudo apt install apt-transport-https ca-certificates curl software-properties-common
> curl -fsSL https://download.docker.com/linux/ubuntu/gpg | sudo apt-key add -
> sudo add-apt-repository "deb [arch=amd64] https://download.docker.com/linux/ubuntu bionic stable"
> sudo apt update && apt-cache policy docker-ce
> sudo apt install docker-ce && sudo apt install docker-compose
```
- To make it able to login docker hub (following to Jenkinsfiles) run
```sh
> sudo chmod 666 /var/run/docker.sock
> dpkg -r --ignore-depends=golang-docker-credential-helpers golang-docker-credential-helpers
```
## Setup Jenkins

- Access Jenkins web : http://<sever ip>:8080
- Copy password form 
```sh
> sudo cat /var/lib/jenkins/secrets/initialAdminPassword
```
- Make Jenkins able to access any files without password.
```sh
> sudo vi /etc/sudoers
```
- Add following line to the end of file.
```sh
jenkins ALL=(ALL) NOPASSWD: ALL
```
- Setting Credential env for use in Jenkinsfile: Manage Jenkins > Mange Credentails > click jenkins (column store) > Global credentails (unrestricted) > Add Credentials
- Add following ID with kind "username with password" and scope "Global"
```sh
DOCKER_HUB (docker hub user:password)
SSH (ssh user:password)
```
## Setup Project

> - Go to Dashboard > New Item 
> - Enter "project name" 
> - Select "Pipline" and Click "OK"
> - Select "GitHub project" 
> - Paste your GitHub project url
> - Build Triggers : select "GitHub hook trigger for GITScm polling"
> - Pipeline : 
-- definition select "Pipeline script from SCM"
-- SCM slect "Git"
-- Repository URL "<your GitHub project url>"
-- Credentails (if your repository have credentails)
-- Branch Specifier "\*/\*" (for any branch)
-- Click Add button select "Check out to specific local branch"
-- Script path "Jenkinsfile"
-- Save
> - Go to your GitHub repository setting
> - Select tab "webhooks" 
> - Add webhooks & paste "http://<Jenkins sever ip>:8080/github-webhook/"
> Copy .env or any secret files to /root/file (have to add script to Jenkinsfile) like show as bellow in stage 'copy secret file'
```sh
sh "sudo cp /root/file/.env ."
sh "sudo cp /root/file/<anyfilesname> ."
```
> - Go to Jenkins Dashboard select your project
> - Click "build Now" to test build
> - Finish !!
##### Commit message should be "0.1:5001:first commit" pattern "<version>:<port>:<message>"

## For Developer 
> - Clone project 
> - Run "docker-compose -f docker-compose.dev.yml up"
> - Enjoy Dev !!
